    "defaultScheme": "dark",
    "version": 1,
    "source": "Inspired by Final Fantasy XI: Vana'diel moonlight, relic-era adventuring, and classical MMO parchment-and-steel UI moods",
    "tokenConvention": "Every color key maps to a CSS custom property named --<key>. e.g. \"accent\" -> var(--accent). The group names (surfaces, lines, text, accents, crystals, states) are for human organization only and are NOT part of the variable name. The four crystal-* tokens are extra identity colors; wire them up where supported.",
    "notExportedYet": "Non-color tokens still live only in styles.css and are intentionally omitted here: --radius, --radius-s, --shadow. For stronger FF11 identity, consider parchment texture overlays in light mode and subtle moonlit vignette in dark mode."
  },
